q) what is private VLAN:

 - it is a type of security feature used in networking to segregate and isolate devices
   within the same VLAN (Virtual Local Area Network).

 types of private VLANs:
    - Primary VLAN: The main VLAN that contains all the devices.
    - Secondary VLANs: These are sub-VLANs within the primary VLAN and can be of two types:
        - Isolated VLAN: Devices in this VLAN cannot communicate with each other but can communicate with devices in the primary VLAN.
        - Community VLAN: Devices in this VLAN can communicate with each other and with devices in the primary VLAN, but not with devices in other community or isolated VLANs.

 benefits of private VLANs:
    - Enhanced security by isolating devices.
    - Reduced broadcast traffic within the VLAN.
    - Improved network management and organization.

use cases of private VLANs:
    - Hosting environments where multiple customers share the same physical infrastructure but need isolation.
    - Data centers to segregate different types of traffic.
    - Enterprises to isolate sensitive devices from the rest of the network.


